# TFM renderer workbench

This page exercises **CommonMark**, ~~GitHub Flavored Markdown~~, [safe links](https://tessyl.com), tables, and every directive in `tfm-directives-1`.

:::tessyl-aside{tone="tip" title="Safe by construction"}
Author strings are escaped, raw HTML fails closed, remote images are blocked by default, and resource IDs cross an explicit authorization boundary.
:::

::tessyl-video[Orbital mechanics demonstration]{asset="asr_video_01JABC" controls=true}

::tessyl-audio[Narrated lesson]{asset="asr_audio_01KABC" transcript="asr_text_01LABC" controls=true}

::tessyl-app[Interactive gravity sandbox]{revision="tsr_01MABC" height="compact"}

::tessyl-data-table[Planet comparison]{dataset="dsr_01NABC" sortable=true}

:::tessyl-infobox{tone="positive" title="Deterministic output"}
The same accepted TFM and authorized resources produce the same semantic HTML.
:::

